    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "## Problem\n\nWe have ~~clint.py~~ `clint.lua` https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36859 for defining custom C lint rules, but we don't have a way to define custom rules for Lua code.\n\n## Expected behavior\n\nIntroduce a build/CI task that allows us to define custom lint rules. Examples:\n\n- disallow use of `assert.truthy`, recommend `ok()` / `eq()` / etc\n- check `it()` descriptions\n- comment format\n- naming conventions\n- ...\n\n## Related\n\n- https://github.com/Kampfkarren/selene claims to be \"Easy to extend and modify\".\n    - Blocked?: https://github.com/Kampfkarren/selene/issues/222\n- `gen_vimdoc.lua` (based on lpeg) has a partial Lua parser.\n- `gen_help_html.lua` (based on treesitter) has some hacky custom rules for help files.\n- https://github.com/lunarmodules/luacheck/issues/37 describes a way to \"extend\" Luacheck by forking/vendoring it.\n- Related issue proposing LuaLS CI check: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/24563",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
